{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"011a3c11-a432-4fcc-886c-2d3522ad58c1","content":"Here are the changes you need:\n\n**Dockerfile additions:**\n\n```dockerfile\n# Create a dumps directory writable by your non-root user\nRUN mkdir -p /tmp/dumps && chown app:app /tmp/dumps\n\n# Enable automatic crash dumps via .NET environment variables\nENV COMPlus_DbgEnableMiniDump=1\nENV COMPlus_DbgMiniDumpType=4\nENV COMPlus_DbgMiniDumpName=/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\n\nUSER app\n```\n\n- `DbgMiniDumpType=4` = full dump with heap (use `1` for a smaller \"mini\" dump).\n- `%p` = PID, `%t` = timestamp, so dumps don't overwrite each other.\n\n**docker run command:**\n\n```bash\ndocker run --cap-add=SYS_PTRACE \\\n  -v /path/on/host/dumps:/tmp/dumps \\\n  your-image\n```\n\n`--cap-add=SYS_PTRACE` is required because `createdump` (the .NET crash dump tool) uses `ptrace` to snapshot the process. Without it, dump collection silently fails.\n\nThe `-v` mount lets you retrieve dumps from the host after a crash.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b09b2164-3243-4f72-89ee-f50ed959f5d2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to set up crash dump collection for a CoreCLR/.NET app in an Alpine-based Docker container running as a non-root user. I'll provide the Dockerfile changes and `docker run` command needed.\n\nKey considerations for Alpine + CoreCLR crash dumps:\n- Alpine uses musl libc, not glibc — createdump is the .NET tool for this\n- Need to set environment variables for .NET crash dump collection\n- Need writable directory for dumps\n- Need `ptrace` capability for createdump (SYS_PTRACE)\n- `/tmp` or a custom directory for dump output\n- Non-root user considerations\n\n\n- Now I'll put together the specific configuration needed to make this work.","outputTokens":476,"requestId":"1B8A:1290CA:E74820:107116C:6A028777"},"id":"36d6b774-0239-40ab-b6eb-102b4b334c94","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:51:00.061Z","parentId":"98c1631e-b92a-4768-8eeb-42a6541aea44"}
